IMPORTANT: Source Data Licenses

This software processes Hindu scripture texts from various sources. The processed
data inherits the licenses of the original sources:

- DharmicData: Open Database License (ODbL-1.0)
  https://github.com/bhavykhatri/DharmicData

- Indian Scriptures: Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 (CC-BY-4.0)
  https://github.com/hrgupta/indian-scriptures

- Project Gutenberg: Public Domain (in the United States)
  https://www.gutenberg.org/

- Sacred-Texts.com: Various (mostly Public Domain and CC-BY)
  https://sacred-texts.com/

- Sanskrit Documents: Various (check individual files)
  https://sanskritdocuments.org/

When using the processed data, please:

1. Respect the original source licenses
2. Attribute the original sources appropriately
3. Do not claim ownership of the scripture texts themselves
4. Share derivative works under compatible licenses

The Hindu scriptures themselves are ancient texts in the public domain. However,
specific translations, commentaries, and compilations may have their own copyrights.
